race.comment: YES LULU (3) good mare who can bounce back with the blinkers going on. Comes to Randwick for the first time after warming up late in the heavy going when third over 1400m at Kembla Grange. Go close. THEBLADE (12) progressive gelding who returns from a let-up. Back in class when a slick on-pace winner over 1300m at Rosehill in fast time. Has a sticky draw to overcome and expected to take a hand in finish. ASGARDA (2) turned in a strong performance at Kembla Grange last start when racing in tougher company, beaten just 0.7L in tricky conditions. The sting out of the ground won't be an issue and Bourke's claim comes in handy. Has the speed to offset the barrier and can make her presence felt. BOJANGLES (4) stuck on well in Midway company last time out and the sting out of the ground is a big tick. Include.
